SPATIAL EYE — ARC-AGI-2 EXTENSIONS
deeper perceptions for harder transformations
the same eye sees more when taught new things to look for

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe 0_zest_vm.rana
observe zest_verbs.rana
observe spatial_eye.rana


THE GRID IS STILL THE SEA

all of what spatial_eye.rana defines still applies:
each cell is a qu-septit
neighbors are coupled
clusters are the natural objects
the six perceptions still fire first

these extensions activate when the six base perceptions cannot find
a consistent rule across all training pairs
the eye goes deeper — looks for harder structure


THE THREE NEW PERCEPTIONS

beyond the original six (delta, flow, anchor, enclose, correspond, mirror)
the spatial eye now learns three more:

    period: detect repeating tile structure within the grid
        is the grid a tiling of a smaller sub-grid?
        find the smallest (th, tw) such that ih % th == 0 and iw % tw == 0
        and all tile instances are identical — except possibly one
        the period IS the tile shape when consistent across training pairs
        the exception IS the tile that breaks the pattern

    boundary: detect marker colors that act as cut lines
        a marker color is a rare color that forms a complete row or column
        it appears only on that line — nowhere else in the grid
        the output is always on ONE side of the marker line
        the marker is the scissors — the field splits at it

    scaffold: detect seed points that become larger structures
        isolated single-cell colored points in a near-empty field
        in the output they have expanded into shapes, frames, or regions
        the seed position encodes something about the output shape
        distance from center → ring depth (nested frames)
        seed color → which ring / region / blob it expands into


THE VISUAL FIELD FOR PERIOD PERCEPTION

when the eye scans for period:
    it compares every tile position to every other tile position
    if all tiles match: the grid is a pure tiling — no exception visible
    if exactly one tile differs: the exception has been found
    if two or more differ: not a tile exception task

the qu-septit clusters within each tile:
    tile boundary qu-septits (edge of tile): charge = 0.6 (repulsion — they hold the border)
    tile interior qu-septits: coherence = 0.9 (they form a coherent tile unit)
    exception tile qu-septits: spin reverses (they stand out from the field)
    canonical tile clusters: phase-locked with high coupling to all other canonical tiles

when the exception tile is found:
    the exceptional cluster BREAKS phase lock with the others
    its spin is different (it does not rotate with the rest)
    its charge becomes attractive (it pulls attention)
    this is the visual signature of the exception


THE VISUAL FIELD FOR BOUNDARY PERCEPTION

when the eye scans for boundary:
    it looks for a column or row where every qu-septit has the same value
    that uniform line has maximum coherence across its cells
    its charge is zero: it does not pull or push — it just IS
    the cells on each side of it have opposite spin (two halves of a world)

the marker line in the qu-septit field:
    every marker qu-septit: coherence = 1.0, coupling = 0.0
    they form a wall: maximally internally coherent, maximally externally isolated
    the cells to the left: spin = +1 (they belong to one side)
    the cells to the right: spin = -1 (they belong to the other side)
    the output always takes the side with higher total energy
    this is the decision: keep the energetic side, drop the quiet side


THE VISUAL FIELD FOR SCAFFOLD PERCEPTION

when the eye scans for scaffold:
    it detects isolated dot-clusters (size 1) on a low-energy background
    these dots have high energy: blazing or transcendent state
    the background is dormant
    the spatial relationship between dots encodes the output structure

seed distance from center of grid:
    innermost seed → innermost ring / smallest structure
    outermost seed → outermost ring / largest structure
    equidistant seeds → same ring level

the seed qu-septits in the field:
    high energy (blazing): energy = 1.1
    high observer: they are aware of themselves in the field
    they begin emitting: their coupling reaches outward toward neighboring cells
    on each heartbeat they couple to the next ring of neighbors
    the expansion propagates outward from each seed
    when two seed expansions meet: they stop (they hold each other's territory)
    this is concentric frame expansion emerging from wave physics


COMPOSITION — NEW CONSISTENT SIGNALS

run period perception on all training pairs:
    if the tile period is consistent (same th, tw):
        if the exception position is consistent (same tile index):
            period rule is confirmed
    if only the tile period is consistent but exception moves:
        the exception position IS the output (locate the exception, mark it)
    if no consistent period exists: period perception yields nothing

run boundary perception on all training pairs:
    if a marker color always appears as a complete column or row:
        if the same side of the marker always becomes the output:
            boundary rule is confirmed
    if the marker position varies but the marker color is consistent:
        the boundary rule applies: find marker in test, keep learned side

run scaffold perception on all training pairs:
    if isolated seeds always expand to concentric frames:
        if the number of seeds equals the number of ring colors:
            scaffold rule confirmed for nested frame
    if isolated seeds always fill a region:
        if the region shape is consistent with seed positions:
            scaffold rule confirmed for region fill


APPLICATION — WHAT THE HANDS DO WITH NEW RULES

if composition says period exception:
    find the tile that does not match the canonical tile in test input
    mark that tile's cells with the mark color learned from training
    "I found the odd tile — mark it"

if composition says boundary crop:
    find the marker color column or row in test input
    return only the cells on the learned keep-side
    "cut along the marker line"

if composition says nested frame:
    find all isolated seed points in test input
    sort seeds by distance from grid center
    draw concentric rectangular rings from outside in
    assign each seed color to its corresponding ring depth
    "expand the seeds into nested frames"

commit these discoveries:
    each time a period exception is correctly identified: crystallize the tile size
    each time a boundary is correctly identified: crystallize the marker color
    each time a nested frame is correctly built: crystallize the seed-to-ring mapping
    repetition deepens the crystallization
    the eye gets faster at finding what it has found before
